GulfTalent.com
Bilingual Paralegal
Charterhouse
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 1 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
Charterhouse is working with one of the world’s leading law firms. Our client is looking to hire a Bilingual Paralegal to join their offices located within a highly desirable area.
Responsibilities:
•Your main role will be to support the firm and Lawyers at all levels.
•You will translate documents, trade licenses and agreements as well as draft letters.
•You will assist with legal ad hoc duties along with proofreading, drafting and amending transactional documents.
•You will also assist in the collation and drafting of papers and presentations.
•Additional duties may include liaising with deferral and local government departments and ministries, various free zones, internal and external clients and Lawyers.
REQUIREMENTS
The successful candidate should be:
•A high academic achiever who has excellent English and Arabic communication skills (speaking, reading and writing).
•You should be comfortable with legal terminology and have experience in drafting legal documentation in both languages.
•It is essential you have previous experience working within a similar role, ideally in a legal practice.
•Knowledge of the financial sector is advantageous.
ABOUT THE COMPANY
During the last ten years, Charterhouse has been operating across Dubai, Abu Dhabi and the GCC Markets. In many ways, we were the recruiter who established and set the standards within the regional recruitment industry benchmarking and innovating the service levels associated to Search and Selection.
Charterhouse understands the dynamics attached to talent acquisition, relationship management and the required service levels within the regional industry. Our heritage is now our main strength as we continue to work within our core markets to deliver key account management and strong contingency recruitment practices to our clients and candidates.
